Sentencas: The sluggish oxygen reduction reaction acts as a vital barrier to the performance enhancement for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells.
Titulo: CuCO2O4-Er0.4Bi1.6O3-δ: An active hybrid cathode for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: In this paper we report a CuCO2O4-Er0.4Bi1.6O3-(delta) composite cathode synthesized via sol-gel and subsequent mechanical mixing methods.
Titulo: CuCO2O4-Er0.4Bi1.6O3-δ: An active hybrid cathode for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The composite cathode contains an electronic conductor CuCO2O4 and an ionic conductor Er0.4Bi1.6O3-delta, dramatically enhancing the oxygen reduction reaction kinetics and the sintering performance.
Titulo: CuCO2O4-Er0.4Bi1.6O3-δ: An active hybrid cathode for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Introduction of the Er0.4Bi1.6O3-delta nanoparticles brings an obvious increase of triple phase boundaries and enhancement of electrochemical activities.
Titulo: CuCO2O4-Er0.4Bi1.6O3-δ: An active hybrid cathode for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: As expected, the composite cathode with addition of 35 wt% of Er0.4Bi1.6O3-delta shows the least polarization resistance of 0.07 Omega cm(2) in air at 800 degrees C.
Titulo: CuCO2O4-Er0.4Bi1.6O3-δ: An active hybrid cathode for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: What's more, the sintering temperature is distinctly reduced from 1000 degrees C to 800 degrees C.
Titulo: CuCO2O4-Er0.4Bi1.6O3-δ: An active hybrid cathode for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells
